    • exceptions.Exception: Common base class for all non-exit exceptions.

      • pyxb.utils.fac.FACError

        • pyxb.utils.fac.UpdateApplicationError: Exception raised when an unsatisfied update instruction is executed.
      • pyxb.exceptions_.PyXBError: Base class for exceptions that indicate a problem that the user probably can't fix.
        • pyxb.exceptions_.LogicError: Raised when the code detects an implementation problem.
          • pyxb.exceptions_.IncompleteImplementationError: Raised when required capability has not been implemented.
        • pyxb.exceptions_.UsageError: Raised when the code detects user violation of an API.
      • pyxb.exceptions_.PyXBException: Base class for exceptions that indicate a problem that the user should fix.
        • pyxb.exceptions_.BadDocumentError: Raised when processing document content and an error is encountered.
          • pyxb.exceptions_.StructuralBadDocumentError: Raised when processing document and the content model is not satisfied.
            • pyxb.exceptions_.UnrecognizedDOMRootNodeError: A root DOM node could not be resolved to a schema element
        • pyxb.exceptions_.BindingError: Raised when the bindings are mis-used.
          • pyxb.exceptions_.NotComplexContentError: An operation that requires a content model was invoked on a complex type instance that has empty or simple content.
          • pyxb.exceptions_.NotSimpleContentError: An operation that requires simple content was invoked on a complex type instance that does not have simple content.
          • pyxb.exceptions_.ReservedNameError: Reserved name set in binding instance.
        • pyxb.exceptions_.BindingGenerationError: Raised when something goes wrong generating the binding classes
        • pyxb.exceptions_.DOMGenerationError: A non-validation error encountered converting bindings to DOM.
          • pyxb.exceptions_.UnboundElementError: An instance converting to DOM had no bound element.
        • pyxb.exceptions_.NamespaceArchiveError: Problem related to namespace archives
        • pyxb.exceptions_.NamespaceError: Violation of some rule relevant to XML Namespaces
          • pyxb.exceptions_.NamespaceUniquenessError: Raised when an attempt is made to record multiple objects of the same name in the same namespace category.
          • pyxb.exceptions_.QNameResolutionError: Raised when a QName cannot be associated with a namespace.
        • pyxb.exceptions_.NotInNamespaceError: Raised when a name is referenced that is not defined in the appropriate namespace.
        • pyxb.exceptions_.PyXBVersionError: Raised on import of a binding generated with a different version of PYXB
        • pyxb.exceptions_.SchemaUniquenessError: Raised when somebody tries to create a schema component using a schema that has already been used in that namespace.
        • pyxb.exceptions_.SchemaValidationError: Raised when the XML hierarchy does not appear to be valid for an XML schema.
        • pyxb.exceptions_.ValidationError: Raised when something in the infoset fails to satisfy a content model or attribute requirement.
          • pyxb.exceptions_.AttributeValidationError: Raised when an attribute requirement is not satisfied.
            • pyxb.exceptions_.AttributeChangeError: Attempt to change an attribute that has a fixed value constraint.
            • pyxb.exceptions_.MissingAttributeError: Raised when an attribute that is required is missing in an element.
            • pyxb.exceptions_.ProhibitedAttributeError: Raised when an attribute that is prohibited is set or referenced in an element.
            • pyxb.exceptions_.UnrecognizedAttributeError: Attempt to reference an attribute not sanctioned by content model.
          • pyxb.exceptions_.ComplexTypeValidationError: Raised when a validation requirement for a complex type is not satisfied.
            • pyxb.exceptions_.AbstractInstantiationError: Attempt to create an instance of an abstract complex type.
            • pyxb.exceptions_.AttributeOnSimpleTypeError: Attempt made to set an attribute on an element with simple type.
            • pyxb.exceptions_.ContentValidationError: Violation of a complex type content model.
              • pyxb.exceptions_.BatchElementContentError: Element/wildcard content cannot be reconciled with the required content model.
                • pyxb.exceptions_.IncompleteElementContentError: Validation of an instance failed to produce an accepting state.
                • pyxb.exceptions_.InvalidPreferredElementContentError: Use of a preferred element led to inability to generate a valid document
                • pyxb.exceptions_.UnprocessedElementContentError: Validation of an instance produced an accepting state but left element material unconsumed.
              • pyxb.exceptions_.ContentNondeterminismExceededError: Content validation exceeded the allowed limits of nondeterminism.
              • pyxb.exceptions_.ExtraSimpleContentError: A complex type with simple content was provided too much content.
              • pyxb.exceptions_.IncrementalElementContentError: Element or element-like content could not be validly associated with an sub-element in the content model.
                • pyxb.exceptions_.UnrecognizedContentError: Element or element-like content could not be validly associated with an sub-element in the content model.
              • pyxb.exceptions_.MixedContentError: Non-element content added to a complex type instance that does not support mixed content.
              • pyxb.exceptions_.NonPluralAppendError: Attempt to append to an element which does not accept multiple instances.
              • pyxb.exceptions_.OrphanElementContentError: An element expected to be used in content is not present in the instance.
              • pyxb.exceptions_.SimpleContentAbsentError: An instance with simple content was not provided with a value.
              • pyxb.exceptions_.UnprocessedKeywordContentError: A complex type constructor was provided with keywords that could not be recognized.
          • pyxb.exceptions_.ElementValidationError: Raised when a validation requirement for an element is not satisfied.
            • pyxb.exceptions_.AbstractElementError: Attempt to create an instance of an abstract element.
            • pyxb.exceptions_.ContentInNilInstanceError: Raised when an element that is marked to be nil is assigned content.
            • pyxb.exceptions_.ElementChangeError: Attempt to change an element that has a fixed value constraint.
            • pyxb.exceptions_.NoNillableSupportError: Raised when invoking _setIsNil on a type that does not support nillable.
          • pyxb.exceptions_.NonElementValidationError: Raised when an element (or a value bound to an element) appears in context that does not permit an element.
          • pyxb.exceptions_.SimpleTypeValueError: Raised when a simple type value does not satisfy its constraints.
            • pyxb.exceptions_.SimpleFacetValueError: Raised when a simple type value does not satisfy a facet constraint.
            • pyxb.exceptions_.SimpleListValueError: Raised when a list simple type contains a member that does not satisfy its constraints.
            • pyxb.exceptions_.SimplePluralValueError: Raised when context requires a plural value.
            • pyxb.exceptions_.SimpleUnionValueError: Raised when a union simple type contains a member that does not satisfy its constraints.
      • exceptions.StandardError: Base class for all standard Python exceptions that do not represent interpreter exiting.
        • exceptions.LookupError: Base class for lookup errors.
          • pyxb.utils.unicode.CodePointSetError: Raised when some abuse of a CodePointSet is detected.
        • exceptions.ValueError: Inappropriate argument value (of correct type).
